text: Rockhouse Island is one of the uninhabited Canadian arctic islands in Kivalliq Region, Nunavut, Canada. It is one of several islands located within the mouth of Chesterfield Inlet. The island is approximately from the Inuit hamlet of Chesterfield Inlet. ==References== Category:Islands of Chesterfield Inlet Category:Uninhabited islands of Kivalliq Region Category:Islands of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago
